STRATEGY "Mean Reversal 5m" VERSION 1.0
DESCRIPTION "Mean Reversal strategy for intraday trading in 5 minute interval candle stick data"
EVALUATION
  SCHEDULE every 5m candle
  TIMING evaluate 2 candles before candle close
RULES SECTION
  INPUTS
    - instrument: BANKNIFTY
    - lot size: 1
    - strike rounding: 0.01
    - risk management: 2% stop loss, 3% target
ENTRY SECTION
  - SHORT ENTRY
    - condition: 20-period EMA < 50-period EMA and price > 20-period EMA
    - condition: RSI(14) > 70
    - condition: Bollinger Bands (20, 2) price < lower band
    - entry logic: SHORT at market price
    - logging: "SHORT ENTRY: EMA crossover, RSI overbought, Bollinger Bands breakout"
EXIT SECTION
  - SHORT EXIT
    - condition: price > 20-period EMA
    - condition: RSI(14) < 30
    - condition: Bollinger Bands (20, 2) price > upper band
    - exit logic: CLOSE at market price
    - priority: 1
    - logging: "SHORT EXIT: EMA crossover, RSI oversold, Bollinger Bands breakout"
  - RE-ENTRY RULES
    - condition: price < 20-period EMA
    - condition: RSI(14) > 50
    - condition: Bollinger Bands (20, 2) price < lower band
    - re-entry logic: SHORT at market price
    - logging: "RE-ENTRY: EMA crossover, RSI overbought, Bollinger Bands breakout"
  - STOP LOSS
    - condition: price < 2% stop loss
    - exit logic: CLOSE at market price
    - priority: 2
    - logging: "STOP LOSS: 2% stop loss triggered"
  - TARGET
    - condition: price > 3% target
    - exit logic: CLOSE at market price
    - priority: 3
    - logging: "TARGET: 3% target achieved"
  - POSITION MANAGEMENT
    - condition: position size > 1 lot
    - condition: risk management: 2% stop loss, 3% target
    - re-entry logic: SHORT at market price
    - logging: "POSITION MANAGEMENT: re-entry with adjusted risk management"